    <IRS990ScheduleO documentId="IRS990ScheduleO" softwareId="24020490" softwareVersionNum="2024v5.2">
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 6</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>A Regular Member is a person paying standard fees for rowing privileges or satisfying requirements in lieu of such fees as set by the Board of Directors. In addition to such Regular Members, the Board of Directors may designate other types of membership including, for example, non-rowing, fitness, non-resident, and the like, and such other types may or may not have membership fees or dues, only as determined by the Board of Directors. Only Regular Members are voting members of the Organization.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 7a</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The Board is elected by Regular Members at the annual membership meeting held in September each year.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section A, Line 7b</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Directors are elected by the vote of the Regular Members of the Organization. Regular Members may vote to remove a Director at any time, with or without good cause. The bylaws of the Organization may be altered, amended, or repealed, and new bylaws may be adopted by the Board of Directors, however, the following amendments may be adopted only by the Regular Members at an annual or special meeting: (a) changing the methods of electing or removing officers; (2) increasing or extending the terms of officers; or (3) increasing the quorum for membership meetings. Any bylaw alteration, amendment, repeal, or restatement adopted by the Board of Directors may be repealed and nullified by majority vote of the Regular Members at an annual or special meeting called no later than sixty days after adoption.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 11b</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The Form 990 is prepared by an external CPA and reviewed by the President and Treasurer before it is finalized and filed.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section B, Line 15a</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>The Executive Director's salary is set by a research process conducted by the Human Resources Committee and approved by the Board of Directors. Comparable salaries are gathered from local organizations as well as similar jobs nationally.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
      <SupplementalInformationDetail>
        <FormAndLineReferenceDesc>Form 990, Part VI, Section C, Line 19</FormAndLineReferenceDesc>
        <ExplanationTxt>Certain documents available upon request.</ExplanationTxt>
      </SupplementalInformationDetail>
    </IRS990ScheduleO>
